benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/renameKey - Update a bundle externalKey

covered: Valid Request: Multiple scenarios (TC01, TC09, TC14, TC19/TC20/TC21/TC22) verify successful updates with valid payloads and headers.
Non-Existing Resource: TC04 (update with non-existent bundleId) and TC15 (no bundles in system) cover handling for missing resources.
Authorization: TC02 (missing required header) and TC12 (unauthorized/missing token) cover header/auth validation.
Concurrency: TC17 tests concurrent updates to the same bundle.
Validation/Error Handling: TC02, TC03, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC11 cover missing headers, malformed body, missing body, invalid JSON, missing externalKey, and edge conditions.

Edge Cases: TC05 (externalKey conflict), TC10 (long externalKey with limits), TC18 (regression on problematic externalKey), TC19 (special characters), TC20 (leading/trailing spaces), TC21 (extra unexpected header) are covered.
Happy Path + Variants: TC01 (happy path), TC14 (reason/comment headers), TC24 (documentation accessibility scenario) provide positive flow and peripheral checks.
gaps: Pagination: No tests covering pagination behavior for large datasets or lists of bundles.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling (e.g., listing/browsing bundles with page size and page number).
Authorization: Consider additional negative/edge authorization scenarios (e.g., invalid token format, expired token, insufficient scopes) beyond missing header.
Caching/Performance: Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and explicit response-time checks under varying load.
Rate Limiting/Throttling: Introduce tests simulating burst requests to verify rate-limiting behavior and graceful degradation (429s if applicable).
Partial Update: Clarify and test whether partial updates are allowed; add a test asserting rejection if partial update is not supported (if applicable).
Consistency under load: Enhance TC17 with explicit assertions for data integrity when concurrent requests complete.
